{{nihongo|'''Nōhi Gokoku Shrine'''|濃飛護國神社|Nōhi Gokoku Jinja}} is a [[Shinto]] [[Shinto shrine|shrine]] located in [[Ōgaki, Gifu|Ōgaki]], [[Gifu Prefecture]], [[Japan]]. It is located near the base of [[Ōgaki Castle]]. The shrine is designated to the approximately 19,000 people from the Seino and Hida regions of Gifu Prefecture who died during wars. Because it represented only a small portion of the prefecture, it was eventually replaced by the [[Gifu Gokoku Shrine]].

==History==
The shrine was originally built in 1871 to honor the 54 men from the area who had died during the [[Boshin War]]. Originally, it was called '''Ōgaki Shōkonsha''' (大垣招魂社). The shrine was replaced by the [[Gifu Gokoku Shrine]] in nearby [[Gifu, Gifu|Gifu]] after it was completed in 1940.

The shrines two festival days are April 23 and September 22.

